Title: Heterotic String Theory with Background Fluxes
Authors: Jan Louis, Andrei Micu
Comments: 27 pages, minor changes
Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B626 (2002) 26-52
\\
  We discuss compactifications of the heterotic string in the presence of
background fluxes. Specifically we consider compactifications on T^6, T^5, K3 x
T^2 and K3 x S^1 for which we derive the bosonic sector of the low energy
effective action. The consistency with the corresponding gauged supergravities
is demonstrated.
